Rating: 4
This was great and so easy to do! My husband loved it. I did not have green onions, so I used a small portion of a vidalia onion. Used red wine vinegar and left out the cilantro. I took another reviewer's advice and used less oil and deglazed the pan with white wine. Gave it a great flavor. Served over rice pilaf/orzo mix (from Near East) and some side veggies (zucchini, asparagus) that I bought at Whole Foods--just needed to heat them up. Overall, a great meal!

